briefdescription.para: Used by the DragCubeSystem when it is generating drag cube entries on startup if none are found for this module. When called the module should set it's model position/setup to match the expected position/orientation when 'name' drag cube is active.

parameterdescription.para: The name of the drag cube to assume the position/setup for.

briefdescription.para: This method will be called from Part class DemoteToPhysicslessPart when the part is being converted from physical to physicsless part. It is called before the joints and rigidbodies are destroyed.
Should return an array of strings that are the drag cube names that this module implements.
This method will be called when this modules part and itself is first disabled (when it is not attached to a vessel) when created in Inventory/Construction mode.
This method is called when a part is being taken out from a slot while being in EVAConstruction mode.

parameterdescription.para: The inventory part module this part is being drawn from.

briefdescription.para: Called when the part is stored in an inventory.

Used by the DragCubeSystem when it is generating drag cube entries on startup if none are found for this module. Should return true if this module is to use procedural drag cubes and false if it is to generate drag cubes for the drag cube names returned in GetDragCubeNames method.
